===Etymology===

[[aza-]] + [[-iridine]].  [[aza|Aza]] denotes a [[monocycle]] with a single nitrogen atom, and [[iridine]] is used to mark a three-membered monocycle.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|əˈzirɪdin}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|organic compound|lang=en}} A three-membered [[heterocycle]] containing two [[methylene]] groups and an [[imine]]; the nitrogen equivalent of [[ethylene oxide]].
# {{context|by extension|lang=en}} Any [[derivative]] of this basic structure.

